The paper discusses the challenges involved in developing a mobile phone app for mental health research using sensor data. The focus is on the technical challenges and acceptability of passive data collection for mental health research. The paper also discusses the potential of mobile phone sensor technology in mental health care. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Computers and Society (cs.CY), Other Computer Science (cs.OH), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
